Content:: Hugo Hofstetter (born 13 February 1994) is a French cyclist, who currently rides for UCI ProTeam Arkéa–Samsic.[4] In August 2020, he was named in the startlist for the 2020 Tour de France.[5] He finished in the top 10 of five stages during the race, including the final stage on the Champs-Élysées.[6] This biographical article related to a French cycling person born in the 1990s is a stub.
